Anne L wrote a review Aug 2023
3 contributions
Amazing Resort and Hotel….didn’t want to leave.
We have just left the Tia Wellness after a 5 night stay as part of a tour of Vietnam…just wow….what an amazing place to stay. We stayed in a one bedroom pool villa near the beach, which was stunning. The hotel facilities and grounds are immaculate and constantly maintained by the hard working staff. Spa facilities and staff are great, as were the staff at breakfast, which had a great variety to choose from. We took advantage of the paddle board use at the beach which was included which is a nice touch. We didn’t use the destination dining, but saw a couple having dinner on the beach, which looked very special. Unfortunately we needed to have the nurse visit on one day, and she was amazing, which sums up all of the staff. Nothing was ever too much trouble for any of the…
We are very pleased that you enjoyed our resort, from the location to the facilities, breakfast any-time to our luxurious garden... which made you didn't want to leave our oasis. Thank you for sharing that you appreciated the kindness of our nurse and all staff. Looking forward to welcoming you again for a private dinner on the beach. Warm regards from TIA Wellness Resort.
